XsDataPacket Class Reference

Contains an interpreted data message. The class provides easy access to the contained data through its many functions. More...

Detailed Description

Contains an interpreted data message. The class provides easy access to the contained data through its many functions.

Constructor & Destructor Documentation

int XsDataPacket::itemOffsetExact ( XsDataIdentifier  id) const
inline

Return the item offset of the supplied data identifier id using strict matching criteria.

This function will search for an exact match of id, including the subformat. Equivalent to XsDataPacket_itemOffsetMasked(thisPtr, id, XDI_FullMask);

Parameters
idThe data identifier to return the offset off
Returns
The offset in the message where the data of this identifier can be found or -1 if it could not be found
See Also
XsDataPacket_itemOffsetLoose
XsDataPacket_itemOffsetMasked

int XsDataPacket::itemOffsetLoose ( XsDataIdentifier  id) const
inline

Return the item offset of the supplied data identifier id using loose matching criteria.

This function will ignore the subformat of the data when searching for id. Equivalent to XsDataPacket_itemOffsetMasked(thisPtr, id, ~XDI_SubFormatMask);

XsMessage XsDataPacket::originalMessage ( void  ) const
inline

Returns a copy the original message of the data packet.

This returns the original message that was last set with setMessage, or in the constructor. Note that if existing data was updated, the original data may have been overwritten, only added data will not be returned in this message. When the packet was constructed from a legacy message, the legacy message will be returned.

See Also
XsDataPacket_originalMessage
Returns
An XsMessage containing a copy of the original message
